)

paragraphs.original:
(to CASSIUS) What said Popillius Lena?
(to
)

paragraphs.translated:
(to CASSIUS) What did Popillius Lena say?
(to
)

paragraphs.original:
Pardon me, Caius Cassius.
The enemies of Caesar shall say this;
Then, in a friend, it is cold modesty.

(aside to BRUTUS) I know not what may fall. I like it not.
(aside to
)

paragraphs.translated:
(to LEPIDUS) Your brother has to die too. Do you agree, Lepidus?
(to
)

paragraphs.original:
(to POET) Get you hence, sirrah. Saucy fellow, hence!
(to
)

paragraphs.translated:
(to POET) Get out of here, you! Get away, you rude fellow!
(to
)

Cicero is dead, by their decree. (to BRUTUS) Have you received letters from your wife, my lord?
(to
)

Go back to sleep, Lucius. Claudio! (to VARRUS) You there, wake up!
(to
)

paragraphs.original:
(returning with LUCILLIUS) Even so, Lucillius.
